<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-19T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-19T04:00:00-05:00" n="703" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d703">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/8729: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-19T18:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">June 19,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 19—2:10
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>211. Abbott telegraphs from Chita under date of June 17th that the town
                            is quiet and that Ungern’s<note n="50" xml:id="d703fn50">Baron Ungern
                                Sternberg, formerly a captain in the Russian Imperial Army, was
                                advancing from Urga, in Mongolia, which he had captured in February
                                1921.</note> forces were confronted [<hi rend="italic">defeated</hi>] by RedArmy near Verkhneudinsk June 6th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>